Story: CLI Greeter Tool - Demonstrates practical CLI argument usage

Given:
  name: String = ARG("--name", "World")
  greeting: String = ARG("--greeting", "Hello")
  shout: Boolean = HAS_FLAG("--shout")
  count: String = ARG("--count", "1")
  times: Number = 0

Step 1 → Parse count as number
  Then: times becomes PARSE_INT count
  Because: Convert string to number

Step 2 → Build the greeting message
  Then: message becomes greeting + ", " + name + "!"
  Because: Construct full greeting

Step 3 → Apply shouting if flag is set
  If shout = true
    Then: message becomes UPPERCASE message
    Because: User requested shouting

Step 4 → Display greeting the specified number of times
  Then: counter becomes 0
  
Step 5 → Print greeting
  If counter < times
    Effect: Print message
    Then: counter becomes counter + 1
    Then: repeat from Step 5

End:
  Return: "Greeter complete"
